item.title: Todd Muller becomes NZ opposition leader
item.description: Little-known opposition agriculture spokesman Todd Muller has seized the leadership of New Zealand's National party and will take on Jacinda Ardern in September's election.

item.title: Sack Labor MP for China spray: Nats deputy
item.description: Labor powerbroker Joel Fitzgibbon has been accused of "weaponising foreign policy" in explosive comments criticising the government's handling of China relations.

item.title: China urges Taiwanese against independence
item.description: China will encourage the people of Taiwan to join it in opposing the island's independence and promoting China's "reunification", Chinese Premier Li Keqiang says, a move likely to worsen Beijing's poor relations with Taipei.

item.title: US naval base shooting terrorism-related
item.description: A shooting at a Texas naval air station that wounded a sailor and left the gunman dead was being investigated as "terrorism-related," the FBI says, but divulged few details as to why.

item.title: AV Jennings slump as home building suffers
item.description: Home builder AV Jennings has moderated its outlook and no longer expects its full year results to better those from 12 months ago, as consumers delay major purchases.

item.title: Another crackdown on class action funders
item.description: Cashed-up backers of class action lawsuits are facing another federal government clampdown.

item.title: Cyclone slams parts of India, Bangladesh
item.description: Wide tracts of coastal India and Bangladesh have been flooded and millions are without power after Cyclone Amphan swept through, killing more than 80 people and cutting a path of destruction.

item.title: New inquiry into Australian water policy
item.description: The Productivity Commission will examine Australia's water reforms in a new inquiry designed to guide governments through the tricky policy area.

item.title: Third murder charge over US jogger death
item.description: The man who videotaped the gunning down of an unarmed black man as he jogged in a suburban neighbourhood in Georgia has been arrested as the third white suspect accused of murder in the racially charged case.

item.title: Record daily virus death toll for Brazil
item.description: Brazil suffered a record 1188 coronavirus deaths on Thursday and is fast approaching Russia to become the world's number two COVID-19 hotspot behind the United States.
